{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PNF_PARAM.response error code handling in vnf_nr_handle_pnf_param_response\n\n### Summary\nThe `vnf_nr_handle_pnf_param_response` function in the VNF NR module was not checking the error_code field of received PNF_PARAM.response messages. This caused the VNF to incorrectly process error responses from the PNF as successful responses, leading to undefined behavior during PNF parameter exchange.\n\nThe issue was identified when PNFs returned error codes but the VNF continued processing as if the parameters were accepted. This resulted in configuration failures that were not properly handled or reported.\n\nThe fix implements proper error code validation following the same pattern used by other NR response handlers in the codebase, ensuring consistent error handling behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf.c`: Added error code check using `NFAPI_NR_PARAM_MSG_OK` before invoking the callback in `vnf_nr_handle_pnf_param_response`\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf.c`: Fixed typo \"reponse\" to \"response\" in trace messages\n\n"
}